# Project Standards

## Source of Truth

- Design values: `docs/design-standards.md`
- Review goals: `docs/testing-goals.md`
- CSS tokens: `app/globals.css`

## Naming

- Files: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g. `product-card.tsx`)
- Components: `PascalCase` (e.g. `ProductCard`)
- CSS classes: Tailwind utilities only — no custom class names outside `globals.css`

## No Magic Numbers

Hardcoded values (company name, phone, address, product specs) must live in a single data file or constant, never inline in JSX.

```tsx
// BAD
<p>+91 20 2712 7873</p>

// GOOD
import { COMPANY } from "@/lib/constants";
<p>{COMPANY.phone}</p>
```

## Data Separation

Product specs, feature lists, and application descriptions go in data objects at the top of the file or in a separate data file — not scattered through JSX.

## TypeScript

- No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow with type guards.
- Use `import type` for type-only imports.
- Define prop types with `interface`, not inline.

## Unused Code

Remove unused imports, components, and variables. Do not leave commented-out code blocks.
